node.text:
Was experimenting with #kwongwohhing sauces - Steam Fish Sauce. No, fish was not involved.
.
I figured most already know how to use this sauce on any fish. Spread fish, add Steam Fish Sauce and steam! Simple & Perfect tasting results for anyone. But how about using it with .... mince Pork or Chicken!
.
This recipe taste best with #kwhsignaturesauces , you will find out why when you taste them yourselves 😉
.
KWH STEAM PORK / CHICKEN BALLS
• 200g mince meat
• 1/2 tbsp sesame oil
• 1/2 tbsp KWH light soya sauce
• 1 tbsp KWH Steam Fish Sauce
• 1/2 cup Coriander stems
• Kei Chee (Goji Berries) 
Marinate ingredients together, form into balls, pop a Goji on each ball and place it on soft tofu to steam, garnish with Coriander leaves. That’s it! That fast.
.
.
KWH FRIED PORK / CHICKEN BALLS
• 200g mince meat
• 1/2 tbsp sesame oil
• 1 tbsp KWH Steam Fish Sauce
• 1/2 cup Coriander stems
Marinated ingredients together and pan fry balls till golden. 
Next, remove oil in pan, add 2 tbsp of KWH Steam Fish Sauce and 2 tbsp of water, mix and heat well, pour over fried pork balls and garnish with coriander leaves. That’s it! 4 ingredients to deliciousness.
.
I’m betting this is going to go so well with pasta too!!
.
KWH Steam Fish Sauce is deliciously unique. It’s savoury like our Teochew fish sauce but enhanced with sweetness from Plums. I’m already thinking of new ideas to pair this and I know it’s going to be good.
.
